1
00:00:53,011 --> 00:00:54,012
Hey.

2
00:00:56,014 --> 00:00:57,015
Thanks.

3
00:00:57,974 --> 00:00:58,975
I'll see you.

4
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:19,079
CLINICAL ACNEOLOGY

5
00:01:50,693 --> 00:01:51,528
Mi-jo.

6
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:54,864
Sorry. I rushed over
without even taking off my makeup.

7
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:56,658
-Go study for your exam.
-Okay.

8
00:02:00,995 --> 00:02:01,996
See you.

9
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,081
Go on.

10
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:11,548
-You?
-Oh, come on.

11
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:13,550
Is Ms. Park Jeong-ja's guardian here?

12
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:14,592
Yes.

13
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:17,303
Goodness, guys.

14
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:19,305
-Oh, right.
-It's me.

15
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,772
Those three care for her
a lot better than any husband would.

16
00:02:27,856 --> 00:02:28,857
I know, right?

17
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:34,654
Mom.

18
00:02:56,009 --> 00:03:03,016
WHEN YOU THINK IT'S THE END

19
00:03:06,644 --> 00:03:08,605
EPISODE 8

20
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:25,121
Mom, let's keep this to ourselves.

21
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,041
Chan-young is sick,

22
00:03:28,124 --> 00:03:30,752
and Joo-hee's having a hard time
because she quit her job.

23
00:03:32,795 --> 00:03:34,589
Come whenever you want.

24
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:37,008
I will

25
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:39,719
tell you everything.

26
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:55,693
-My gosh.
-What's going on?

27
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:00,615
Did you drink?

28
00:04:01,324 --> 00:04:02,992
Did you drive?

29
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:04,494
I can't sleep.

30
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:07,747
But you need to sleep.
You have work tomorrow.

31
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:09,666
Honey, get out of bed.

32
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,251
Come here.

33
00:04:12,085 --> 00:04:15,421
Why did you guys even move out
if you were going to come so often?

34
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:17,131
Goodness.

35
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:21,886
Do you want some warm milk?

36
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:23,179
I'm sleepy.

37
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:52,917
Bye, Mom.

38
00:04:54,043 --> 00:04:55,878
Stop wandering around

39
00:04:56,462 --> 00:04:58,089
and just get some more sleep.

40
00:04:58,172 --> 00:04:59,632
What? I'm going to work.

41
00:04:59,716 --> 00:05:01,509
Mi-jo told me what happened.

42
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:04,470
And your acting is horrible, so just stop.

43
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:09,017
Mom, I'm looking

44
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,311
for a job at another--

45
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:13,438
Stop working at department stores.

46
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:17,233
You've worked long and hard enough
in that suffocating environment.

47
00:05:17,817 --> 00:05:19,319
You can stop now.

48
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:20,236
Momâ€¦

49
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:25,491
Just take a break.

50
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:28,202
It's time you got married.

51
00:05:28,995 --> 00:05:29,954
That's not easy.

52
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:34,751
At least send your profile
to a matchmaking agency.

53
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:44,844
Where's Dad?

54
00:05:44,927 --> 00:05:45,928
He went golfing.

55
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:51,059
-Mom.
-Yes?

56
00:05:51,142 --> 00:05:53,227
When you're pregnant with a baby,

57
00:05:54,103 --> 00:05:55,480
do you bond with it?

58
00:05:56,564 --> 00:05:57,398
Are you pregnant?

59
00:05:58,983 --> 00:06:00,151
Of course not.

60
00:06:00,234 --> 00:06:02,695
Then why are you even asking?

61
00:06:04,197 --> 00:06:05,198
You know,

62
00:06:06,949 --> 00:06:09,202
I was never inside your belly.

63
00:06:10,411 --> 00:06:13,831
Does that mean the bond
between you and me is weaker than the one

64
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:15,958
between you and Mi-hyeon?

65
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,211
You're being strange.

66
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:21,714
It's not like you to ask such a question.

67
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:26,844
Mi-jo.

68
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:31,557
Although you never grew inside my belly,

69
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:34,060
I cared for you as if you did.

70
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:40,358
"I wonder if that kid will like me."

71
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:44,070
"I wonder if she'll like this house."

72
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:48,282
"I wonder what she's thinking.
She's so full of laughter."

73
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,368
"She must be in a good mood."

74
00:06:51,035 --> 00:06:53,371
"I want her to always be happy."

75
00:06:53,454 --> 00:06:55,957
"I wonder what makes her smile."

76
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:01,754
I checked on you
and thought about you, day and night.

77
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,966
That's pretty much the same thing.

78
00:07:05,049 --> 00:07:08,177
Whether or not I was pregnant with you
doesn't really matter.

79
00:07:11,347 --> 00:07:12,181
What is it?

80
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:14,642
Is something wrong?

81
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:17,395
No.

82
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:22,692
Ever since

83
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:25,194
I was little,

84
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:28,072
I've loved it when people said

85
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:30,450
that I take after you.

86
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:33,244
It put me at ease

87
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:35,955
because it meant that I actually do

88
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:38,833
look like your daughter.

89
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:41,210
I'm starting to feel upset.

90
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:43,796
You don't just look like it.
You are my daughter.

91
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:47,133
You know that's not what I meant.

92
00:07:47,925 --> 00:07:49,969
I'm serious right now.

93
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:54,140
I also have something to tell you.

94
00:07:55,099 --> 00:07:56,017
What?

95
00:07:56,726 --> 00:07:58,186
To be honest,

96
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:00,897
if I gave birth to you,

97
00:08:01,397 --> 00:08:03,816
you wouldn't have come out
looking so pretty.

98
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:07,612
Look at your sister.
You know what I mean, right?

99
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:10,781
I can't believe you!

100
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:15,912
Don't tell Mi-hyeon.

101
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:17,872
She's very sensitive about her looks.

102
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:19,457
My goodness.

103
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:23,628
Come to think of it,

104
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:27,673
what am I going to wear to work?
I have a patient in the morning.

105
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:30,092
You can wear Mi-hyeon's clothes. Hold on.

106
00:08:48,277 --> 00:08:49,862
Do you think this is okay?

107
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:52,073
-Hello.
-Hello.

108
00:08:52,156 --> 00:08:54,283
Hey. What?

109
00:08:55,076 --> 00:08:56,577
These are her clothes.

110
00:08:58,246 --> 00:09:00,915
Why are you wearing my clothes?

111
00:09:00,998 --> 00:09:02,625
Those sneakers are mine too.

112
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:07,296
SO-WON

113
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:11,676
Have a good one.

114
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:13,010
-You too.
-You too.

115
00:09:22,144 --> 00:09:23,187
Hey.

116
00:09:23,271 --> 00:09:25,439
Seon-u, were you busy during the weekend?

117
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:26,899
I had to attend a wedding.

118
00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:27,942
When should we eat?

119
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:31,529
I'm busy with work.
I'll go once things are settled.

120
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:33,406
-Okay.
-Bye.

121
00:09:38,119 --> 00:09:41,080
I want you to apologize to So-won.

122
00:09:41,664 --> 00:09:44,083
Apologize? For what?

123
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:46,043
I just let her live her life.

124
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:48,754
She agreed to it,
which is why she accepted it.

125
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:50,339
You coerced her.

126
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:54,385
It's not like I blackmailed her
or threatened her with a knife.

127
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:59,098
So-won is unbelievable.

128
00:09:59,181 --> 00:10:02,184
What's the point of returning
this money after all this time?

129
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:05,187
I could tell by the look in her eyes
as she grew up

130
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:07,565
-that she was really something.
-Father.

131
00:10:07,648 --> 00:10:09,734
She insisted on leaving.

132
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:12,653
I only asked her to sign
the inheritance disclaimer,

133
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:15,656
but she got upset
and wanted to disown the family.

134
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:18,284
-I don't owe her an apology.
-You adopted her,

135
00:10:18,367 --> 00:10:21,495
which means she's our family
and has the right to everything.

136
00:10:21,579 --> 00:10:22,997
Are you insane?

137
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:26,709
Why would I give my hard-earned money
to an adopted child?

138
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:28,794
Do you really mean that?

139
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:32,840
It's time you stopped
hanging around with orphans.

140
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:33,966
I got rid of one,

141
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:36,093
but you're dating another orphan here?

142
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:43,726
Come back to the States with me
so your Green Card won't be taken away.

143
00:10:43,809 --> 00:10:45,519
Don't even think about coming back.

144
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:47,063
Find a job in the States.

145
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:03,829
Why are you standing there?

146
00:11:04,914 --> 00:11:07,833
Even if your hair looks nice,
it's obvious you slept out.

147
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:10,086
At least my hair will look nice.

148
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:13,673
What kind of woman who's about to turn 40

149
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:16,634
goes to her parent's house to sleep out?

150
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:19,136
Couldn't you go somewhere better?

151
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:21,430
Like where?

152
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:24,141
For example,

153
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:26,310
Kim Seon-u's place.

154
00:11:31,857 --> 00:11:33,526
Do I look weird?

155
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:36,320
It's nice. You look like a quack.

156
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:38,614
How about I just wear only my bra inside?

157
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:40,950
Good idea. Way to look insane.

158
00:11:41,033 --> 00:11:43,702
How could you leave only
a sweatsuit at our parents' house?

159
00:11:44,286 --> 00:11:46,414
Why would I want to look nice there?

160
00:11:46,497 --> 00:11:47,998
It's all about comfort.

161
00:11:48,624 --> 00:11:50,251
And you're one to talk.

162
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:53,462
You never leave anything there.
What are you, a stranger?

163
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,715
Don't say that. A stranger?

164
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:58,884
Are you trying to say
I'm not your real family?

165
00:12:00,594 --> 00:12:02,430
I haven't seen you like this in a while.

166
00:12:03,097 --> 00:12:06,475
Okay, fine. Don't be upset.

167
00:12:07,601 --> 00:12:11,105
Mi-jo, you're my beloved,
one and only sister

168
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:14,108
who means so much to me.

169
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:19,071
But stop acting up.
It really pisses me off, okay?

170
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:24,326
This is a semi-basement,
but you still get a lot of sunlight.

171
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:26,412
It's really spacious too.

172
00:12:26,495 --> 00:12:30,332
And it's impossible
to find a place like this at this price.

173
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:34,628
The landlord is very kind,
so tenants end up staying for a long time.

174
00:12:34,712 --> 00:12:35,754
I see.

175
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:38,466
Didn't you also stay here
for quite a while?

176
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:40,259
-Oh, yes.
-Right.

177
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:43,053
Where are you moving to? Nearby?

178
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:44,555
No.

179
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:48,559
I see. If you're done looking around,
you can check out the extra space.

180
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:49,977
-Sure.
-Okay.

181
00:13:01,739 --> 00:13:02,615
Hello?

182
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:04,950
Yes.

183
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:09,330
Oh, really?

184
00:13:11,373 --> 00:13:12,875
Sure.

185
00:13:13,501 --> 00:13:15,127
Okay. Thank you.

186
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:16,295
Thank you.

187
00:13:22,176 --> 00:13:23,511
I'm so excited.

188
00:13:32,478 --> 00:13:34,688
I'll get out here.

189
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:37,733
How much is it?

190
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:38,943
It's 6,000 won.

191
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:54,375
Miss?

192
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:56,961
Yes, here you go.

193
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:04,969
Come in.

194
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:08,264
Hey.

195
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:10,683
You didn't eat, did you?

196
00:14:11,475 --> 00:14:12,560
No. You?

197
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:13,936
Me neither.

198
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:15,062
Let's drink this.

199
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:18,274
Thanks.

200
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,408
Thank you for this.

201
00:14:29,743 --> 00:14:32,746
Is something up with So-won?

202
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:34,957
No.

203
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:39,003
It seemed like you went for a run.
You even skipped lunch.

204
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:42,506
It's nice to get your attention.

205
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:45,509
Why didn't you eat?

206
00:14:47,261 --> 00:14:49,805
Oh, you went home to get changed.

207
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:53,976
Come in.

208
00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:58,147
Are you both on a diet?

209
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:01,609
She doesn't need to go on a diet.

210
00:15:03,235 --> 00:15:04,236
How annoying.

211
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:09,909
Dr. Kim, you need to go to the States
because of your Green Card, right?

212
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:11,201
Yes, that's right.

213
00:15:11,285 --> 00:15:14,705
I'll be back right away.
It won't take long, so don't worry.

214
00:15:15,289 --> 00:15:16,957
Dr. Cha, when's the seminar?

215
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:18,709
Make sure the dates don't overlap.

216
00:15:20,461 --> 00:15:22,254
You're going to the States?

217
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:23,839
Yes.

218
00:15:24,423 --> 00:15:28,636
I was going to go in the summer,
but it turns out I need to go earlier.

219
00:15:29,303 --> 00:15:30,679
It won't take long.

220
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:34,642
Also, my parentsâ€¦

221
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:37,353
In other words, her parents

222
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:40,564
would like to eat with you sometime.
Can you make time?

223
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,566
Why?

224
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:44,109
Why do you think?

225
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:46,445
Maybe to ask about you two,

226
00:15:46,528 --> 00:15:48,906
to see if he's adjusting well
at work, and so on.

227
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:51,116
There could be many reasons.

228
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:57,039
Dr. Kim, is your father still in Seoul?

229
00:15:57,122 --> 00:16:00,668
He doesn't come here often,
so why don't you ask him to join as well?

230
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:01,669
No.

231
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:11,345
I don't think it's the right time.

232
00:16:15,432 --> 00:16:16,850
I guess you're right.

233
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:19,478
He doesn't come often, so I bet he's busy.

234
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:22,648
Then I guess you could just eat with us

235
00:16:22,731 --> 00:16:24,316
when you have time.

236
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,484
That's all right.

237
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:29,113
You guys should get to work.

238
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:30,739
Let's go, Dr. Cha.

239
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:38,998
Have a good day.

240
00:16:39,081 --> 00:16:40,708
Okay. Thanks for the drink.

241
00:16:58,017 --> 00:17:00,686
You're all done.
It didn't hurt too much, did it?

242
00:17:00,769 --> 00:17:02,521
Not as much as I thought it would.

243
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:05,524
Wait here. It's time for your skin care.

244
00:17:05,607 --> 00:17:06,483
Okay.

245
00:17:18,078 --> 00:17:19,038
No.

246
00:17:19,121 --> 00:17:21,582
I don't think it's the right time.

247
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:38,891
You should apply a lot of serum
after receiving laser treatment.

248
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:41,435
That feels nice.

249
00:17:41,518 --> 00:17:42,519
It does, right?

250
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,397
You should apply it regularly.

251
00:17:45,481 --> 00:17:46,356
Okay.

252
00:17:58,994 --> 00:17:59,995
Hey.

253
00:18:01,830 --> 00:18:02,998
I'm working.

254
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:06,376
Really?

255
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:08,337
You really got it?

256
00:18:14,426 --> 00:18:15,427
Hello?

257
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:18,555
Seriously?

258
00:18:18,639 --> 00:18:21,850
I'm so happy for you!

259
00:18:21,934 --> 00:18:25,395
I knew you'd make it.

260
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:28,899
This calls for a party.

261
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:30,734
What time?

262
00:18:31,401 --> 00:18:33,028
But my part-time job--

263
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:34,738
We're going to close early today.

264
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:36,990
What? Why?

265
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:38,575
I have plans.

266
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:42,663
Okay, I'll talk to you later.

267
00:18:42,746 --> 00:18:43,747
Bye.

268
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,794
Are you closing early for me?

269
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:51,421
No.

270
00:18:53,006 --> 00:18:54,591
I have important plans tonight.

271
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:03,475
CONGRATULATIONS,
ACTRESS JEONG CHAN-YOUNG

272
