00:36:41,908 --> 00:36:43,534
-I'll see you.
-Bye.

539
00:36:58,466 --> 00:36:59,300
Go on.

540
00:37:10,978 --> 00:37:13,231
Let's call Chan-young tomorrow.

541
00:37:13,314 --> 00:37:16,234
Okay. Drive safely.

542
00:37:16,317 --> 00:37:17,568
You must be tired.

543
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:18,653
I'm okay.

544
00:37:21,614 --> 00:37:22,615
Joo-hee.

545
00:37:23,199 --> 00:37:24,200
Yes?

546
00:37:25,826 --> 00:37:27,870
Make sure your mom takes her meds.

547
00:37:28,788 --> 00:37:31,540
Why are you suddenly
concerned about my mom?

548
00:37:32,541 --> 00:37:34,252
Let's be good to our parents.

549
00:37:35,962 --> 00:37:37,296
Right. Let's.

550
00:37:38,214 --> 00:37:39,715
-I'll see you.
-Bye.

551
00:37:49,183 --> 00:37:50,768
-Bye.
-Bye.

552
00:38:22,675 --> 00:38:24,677
Come whenever you want.

553
00:38:26,053 --> 00:38:27,680
I will tell you everything.

554
00:38:29,682 --> 00:38:30,599
No.

555
00:38:33,352 --> 00:38:35,604
I don't think it's the right time.

556
00:38:47,742 --> 00:38:49,243
Where is she?

557
00:39:12,767 --> 00:39:13,768
Gosh.

558
00:39:23,736 --> 00:39:24,904
This is driving me crazy.

559
00:39:37,375 --> 00:39:38,793
We haven't done this in ages.

560
00:39:38,876 --> 00:39:43,130
I normally ate lunch and dinner
with my friends or colleagues.

561
00:39:43,714 --> 00:39:46,467
But I always had to eat breakfast alone.

562
00:39:49,261 --> 00:39:51,514
It's always like this
with parents and children.

563
00:39:52,181 --> 00:39:54,100
They fight like cats and dogs,

564
00:39:54,183 --> 00:39:57,144
but all it takes is
a simple meal to reconcile.

565
00:39:58,437 --> 00:39:59,605
Are you leaving tomorrow?

566
00:39:59,688 --> 00:40:00,773
When will you be back?

567
00:40:01,482 --> 00:40:03,150
It's time you came back.

568
00:40:03,651 --> 00:40:06,445
You worked so hard to get a Green Card.
You don't belong here.

569
00:40:07,238 --> 00:40:10,825
I'd also love for us
to have breakfast together

570
00:40:11,534 --> 00:40:12,535
and meet more often.

571
00:40:16,455 --> 00:40:17,289
Father.

572
00:40:17,998 --> 00:40:19,625
-Yes?
-But at this rate,

573
00:40:20,126 --> 00:40:21,961
that won't ever be possible.

574
00:40:23,963 --> 00:40:26,882
So-won is my little sister.

575
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:29,009
She may not be your daughter,

576
00:40:29,677 --> 00:40:30,970
but she's still my sister.

577
00:40:31,887 --> 00:40:32,805
What's your point?

578
00:40:33,389 --> 00:40:36,142
I get that you have no desire
to apologize to her.

579
00:40:36,934 --> 00:40:38,060
But if you don't

580
00:40:39,228 --> 00:40:41,856
apologize to So-won,

581
00:40:44,733 --> 00:40:46,735
I'll have to cut ties with you.

582
00:40:51,365 --> 00:40:52,366
Iâ€¦

583
00:40:53,367 --> 00:40:56,412
worked so hard to raise you well,
and this is what I get in return?

584
00:40:56,495 --> 00:40:57,496
I'm sorry, Father.

585
00:40:57,580 --> 00:41:01,542
Why are you making
such a fuss for the orphan?

586
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:04,587
You may have used her
to get what you wanted,

587
00:41:04,670 --> 00:41:07,506
but Mom and I welcomed her
into the family with love.

588
00:41:08,174 --> 00:41:11,552
I'm the one who paid
for her education and college tuition.

589
00:41:11,635 --> 00:41:15,097
You ruined her life because you didn't
want to share your money with her.

590
00:41:15,181 --> 00:41:16,307
You littleâ€¦

591
00:41:20,811 --> 00:41:23,814
Enjoy all that wealth on your own.

592
00:41:23,898 --> 00:41:25,316
I don't want it either.

593
00:41:25,399 --> 00:41:26,609
I paid for your--

594
00:41:26,692 --> 00:41:29,236
I'll pay you back.

595
00:41:30,196 --> 00:41:33,407
Also, Mi-jo is someone I love dearly.

596
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:37,828
Don't ever talk badly about her.
She's an amazing person.

597
00:41:41,749 --> 00:41:42,750
Have a safe flight.

598
00:41:52,551 --> 00:41:54,512
Your dad went and bought abalone.

599
00:41:54,595 --> 00:41:57,848
I chopped them into small pieces
because you don't like them big.

600
00:41:57,932 --> 00:42:01,143
It's going to be so smooth
that it'll just slide down your throat.

601
00:42:01,769 --> 00:42:03,312
I prefer chewing on abalones.

602
00:42:03,395 --> 00:42:07,024
See? I told you not to chop them
into small pieces.

603
00:42:07,691 --> 00:42:11,153
I thought you didn't like
the texture of abalones.

604
00:42:11,862 --> 00:42:13,364
My palate has changed.

605
00:42:14,907 --> 00:42:16,492
I'll add bigger bites for lunch.

606
00:42:16,575 --> 00:42:18,827
Again? I'm having porridge again?

607
00:42:18,911 --> 00:42:22,456
It helps you absorb nutrients.
Just eat it.

608
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:24,959
I'm not sick enough to have porridge yet.

609
00:42:25,709 --> 00:42:26,961
Later on, I'll have toâ€¦

610
00:42:32,049 --> 00:42:34,426
Here. Eat this.

611
00:42:39,181 --> 00:42:41,725
Pack me the rest for lunch.
I'll eat it at home.

612
00:42:42,351 --> 00:42:44,270
-You're leaving already?
-Go tomorrow.

613
00:42:44,853 --> 00:42:46,939
I have to take care of something.

614
00:42:47,022 --> 00:42:48,649
I need to vacate the studio too.

615
00:42:48,732 --> 00:42:50,025
There's a lot to do.

616
00:42:56,198 --> 00:42:57,658
I'll come this weekend.

617
00:42:58,701 --> 00:43:00,077
Your dad will pick you up.

618
00:43:00,160 --> 00:43:01,453
I can come on my own.

619
00:43:01,537 --> 00:43:03,330
Don't bother. I'll go pick you up.

620
00:43:08,043 --> 00:43:11,213
Right, I always loved riding the truck.

621
00:43:15,342 --> 00:43:18,053
But can you unload
the green onions this time?

622
00:43:18,137 --> 00:43:19,763
I can't stand the smell.

623
00:43:20,347 --> 00:43:22,057
Gosh, I'll have the truck cleaned.

624
00:43:22,141 --> 00:43:23,183
-Get a new car.
-Okay.

625
00:43:24,435 --> 00:43:26,353
-What?
-Get a new car.

626
00:43:26,437 --> 00:43:27,938
Get a sedan.

627
00:43:28,022 --> 00:43:28,939
Really?

628
00:43:29,565 --> 00:43:30,816
Really? A sedan?

629
00:43:31,984 --> 00:43:34,612
Then is it okay if I buy one today?

630
00:43:34,695 --> 00:43:36,989
Get one that's available right away,
even if it's expensive.

631
00:43:37,072 --> 00:43:38,657
This is unbelievable.

632
00:43:39,617 --> 00:43:41,160
Are we really getting a sedan?

633
00:43:41,243 --> 00:43:43,662
My gosh. Dad, do you remember?

634
00:43:43,746 --> 00:43:46,373
We went to a department store
in our truck,

635
00:43:46,457 --> 00:43:48,792
and the receptionist threw a fit

636
00:43:49,585 --> 00:43:53,213
saying we weren't allowed
to park our truck in the parking lot.

637
00:43:53,297 --> 00:43:56,467
Mom almost cussed at her
saying we were customers too.

638
00:43:56,550 --> 00:43:59,303
"Almost"? She kind of did.

639
00:43:59,386 --> 00:44:01,055
-That wench.
-Enough.

640
00:44:02,723 --> 00:44:05,476
Eat your porridge. It's going to get cold.

641
00:44:06,518 --> 00:44:07,561
I'm eating.

642
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:09,188
-Eat up.
-Here.

643
00:44:34,254 --> 00:44:36,048
Sorry, we're not open yetâ€¦

644
00:44:37,257 --> 00:44:39,426
I'm giving all your gifts back.

645
00:44:39,510 --> 00:44:40,427
Throw out my gifts.

646
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:43,097
Have a good life.

647
00:44:51,063 --> 00:44:52,314
Hands off.

648
00:45:05,411 --> 00:45:06,578
Take it back.

649
00:45:10,082 --> 00:45:10,916
No, thanks.

650
00:45:12,042 --> 00:45:14,044
Take it while I'm being nice.

651
00:45:14,128 --> 00:45:17,631
Or I'll start cussing at you and
you'll regret it like many others did.

652
00:45:19,216 --> 00:45:20,968
What's it to you, old lady?

653
00:45:23,929 --> 00:45:25,681
I'm not an old lady.

654
00:45:26,390 --> 00:45:28,642
Anyway, just take it back.

655
00:45:28,725 --> 00:45:32,020
It's better to end things amicably.
Or you'll regret it later.

656
00:45:32,104 --> 00:45:34,690
Gosh, you're getting on my nerves.

657
00:45:36,275 --> 00:45:40,070
I'm sure he put a lot of thought
into picking out these gifts for you.

658
00:45:40,154 --> 00:45:42,489
Each gift shows how much he loved you.

659
00:45:42,573 --> 00:45:44,867
You can't just
throw his gifts away like this

660
00:45:44,950 --> 00:45:46,910
just because you can no longer see that.

661
00:45:46,994 --> 00:45:48,871
You loved him too.

662
00:45:49,371 --> 00:45:52,166
You should treat each other with respect.

663
00:45:54,668 --> 00:45:57,254
If you want to throw it away,
do it yourself.

664
00:45:57,337 --> 00:46:00,382
I'll kill you if you throw it away
in this neighborhood.

665
00:46:02,134 --> 00:46:03,927
Who do you think you are?

666
00:46:06,722 --> 00:46:07,723
Me?

667
00:46:08,599 --> 00:46:11,310
I'm a part-timer at a Chinese restaurant.

668
00:46:23,822 --> 00:46:24,948
Are you going somewhere?

669
00:46:25,032 --> 00:46:27,534
So-won's coming,
and I wanted to invite you to lunch.

670
00:46:28,118 --> 00:46:28,994
I have plans.

671
00:46:29,077 --> 00:46:30,287
Oh, I see.

672
00:46:30,370 --> 00:46:32,289
When are you going to the States?

673
00:46:32,372 --> 00:46:34,958
Tell me your schedule in advance
so I can check mine.

674
00:46:35,626 --> 00:46:36,668
I'm not going.

675
00:46:37,252 --> 00:46:38,837
What about your Green Card?

676
00:46:38,921 --> 00:46:41,548
I'm going to live here,
so I don't need it anymore.

677
00:46:45,552 --> 00:46:48,055
Why are you being so capricious,

678
00:46:48,764 --> 00:46:49,598
Mr. Kim?

679
00:46:54,019 --> 00:46:57,105
You're returning right after lunch, right?
I'm going to be late.

680
00:47:15,457 --> 00:47:16,542
Are you okay?

681
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:26,301
I told her that she should take it back,

682
00:47:26,385 --> 00:47:28,554
and she agreed with me.

683
00:47:29,137 --> 00:47:30,931
Hye-jin is a kind girl.

684
00:47:31,014 --> 00:47:31,974
That's good.

685
00:47:35,102 --> 00:47:37,896
Just go apologize to her
if you didn't mean what you said.

686
00:47:42,693 --> 00:47:43,860
I was torn for a bit.

687
00:47:45,404 --> 00:47:47,990
"Should I close the restaurant
and go back to the hotel

688
00:47:48,615 --> 00:47:49,992
since it's what she wanted?"

689
00:47:53,412 --> 00:47:57,291
But this could always happen again
even if I go back to being a hotel chef.

690
00:47:59,293 --> 00:48:02,212
It's not her fault. We're just different.

691
00:48:05,173 --> 00:48:07,926
How does the tea taste? It came in today.

692
00:48:08,802 --> 00:48:10,387
-It's bitter.
-It's bitter?

693
00:48:11,638 --> 00:48:12,639
Doesn't it smell nice?

694
00:48:29,114 --> 00:48:30,532
Eat this too.

695
00:48:30,616 --> 00:48:33,035
Okay, thanks. You should eat too.

696
00:48:50,135 --> 00:48:50,969
Mom.

697
00:48:53,180 --> 00:48:54,514
What took youâ€¦

698
00:48:56,558 --> 00:48:58,352
so long to tell me the truth?

699
00:48:59,770 --> 00:49:03,523
I just can't help but want to know that.

700
00:49:05,567 --> 00:49:07,361
It must've eaten at you

701
00:49:08,070 --> 00:49:10,322
since you first met me
when I was in high school.

702
00:49:12,366 --> 00:49:13,450
Because you wereâ€¦

703
00:49:15,369 --> 00:49:17,204
so beautiful and pure-hearted.

704
00:49:18,497 --> 00:49:21,958
When you first came into my snack bar,

705
00:49:22,459 --> 00:49:27,297
I couldn't believe how beautiful
and pure-hearted you were.

706
00:49:28,340 --> 00:49:29,591
But when I heard you

707
00:49:31,093 --> 00:49:33,345
talk about your biological mother,

708
00:49:37,099 --> 00:49:39,893
my heart sank.

709
00:49:42,020 --> 00:49:43,313
I never thought

710
00:49:44,356 --> 00:49:49,069
that I'd get to see you grow up
for such a long time.

711
00:49:49,653 --> 00:49:51,363
Fate can be so funny.

712
00:49:53,281 --> 00:49:57,494
You could've just told me.

713
00:50:01,415 --> 00:50:03,417
As time went by,
you became more beautiful.

714
00:50:04,835 --> 00:50:07,546
You were always so radiant.

715
00:50:10,298 --> 00:50:12,634
So I couldn'tâ€¦

716
00:50:18,056 --> 00:50:19,558
I guess she's a disappointment.

717
00:50:21,268 --> 00:50:22,602
My biological mother, I mean.

718
00:50:25,230 --> 00:50:26,815
Do you want to know?

719
00:51:07,189 --> 00:51:10,066
YEONGWOL PRISON
INMATE NUMBER 2382, LEE GYEONG-SUK

720
00:51:24,664 --> 00:51:27,000
Seon-u, do you not eat breakfast?

721
00:51:27,584 --> 00:51:28,418
I eat toast.

722
00:51:28,502 --> 00:51:31,338
Then why do you look so famished?
Slow down a bit.

723
00:51:31,421 --> 00:51:33,006
This is my first meal today.

724
00:51:34,049 --> 00:51:35,801
Maybe it's because I feel better now.

725
00:51:37,135 --> 00:51:39,012
I suddenly have an appetite.

726
00:51:39,971 --> 00:51:42,766
Anyway, it takes me longer
to come here now.

727
00:51:42,849 --> 00:51:45,560
Take that into consideration
next time we eat together.

728
00:51:45,644 --> 00:51:47,604
I'll get you a small car.

729
00:51:48,355 --> 00:51:50,857
No, it's okay. I rarely go anywhere.

730
00:51:50,941 --> 00:51:54,110
No. Let's go check out some cars
since you're out here.

731
00:51:54,194 --> 00:51:56,029
Pick one you like.

732
00:51:56,112 --> 00:51:59,074
You don't owe me a car.
I'll buy it myself if I need one.

733
00:51:59,950 --> 00:52:01,660
But you returned the money to Father.

734
00:52:01,743 --> 00:52:02,577
You're broke.

735
00:52:07,290 --> 00:52:08,708
Did the director tell you?

736
00:52:08,792 --> 00:52:10,961
I'm the one who delivered the money.

737
00:52:11,044 --> 00:52:12,003
What?

738
00:52:12,712 --> 00:52:14,881
I wasn't there for you,

739
00:52:18,677 --> 00:52:19,928
and I feel so bad.

740
00:52:22,472 --> 00:52:25,392
While you were making
such painful decisions by yourself,

741
00:52:26,810 --> 00:52:30,689
I had no idea because I was busy
working at the hospital.

742
00:52:33,358 --> 00:52:35,360
I wouldn't have told you
even if you were jobless.

743
00:52:36,111 --> 00:52:37,195
Why?

744
00:52:39,114 --> 00:52:42,158
Because I wanted to keep
a good relationship with you.

745
00:52:45,829 --> 00:52:49,457
If I told you everything,
you would've suffered too.

746
00:52:50,208 --> 00:52:51,042
Just like now.

747
00:52:52,460 --> 00:52:53,795
I'm completely fine.

748
00:52:55,380 --> 00:52:56,506
It's all clear now.

749
00:52:58,425 --> 00:52:59,968
Now I know

750
00:53:01,011 --> 00:53:02,846
exactly what I need to do.

751
00:53:03,597 --> 00:53:05,307
That's why my appetite is back.

752
00:53:11,688 --> 00:53:12,689
Thank you.

753
00:53:16,943 --> 00:53:18,111
I'm sorry.

754
00:53:25,285 --> 00:53:26,286
Eat this.

755
00:53:35,503 --> 00:53:36,671
You crossed the line.

756
00:53:36,755 --> 00:53:38,465
You're in no place to say that.

757
00:53:39,299 --> 00:53:41,843
I get that you feel anxious.

758
00:53:41,927 --> 00:53:44,304
But you shouldn't have told my parents.

759
00:53:44,387 --> 00:53:46,806
Do you really think so?
How selfish of you.

760
00:53:48,433 --> 00:53:50,185
Then let me be selfish one more time.

761
00:53:51,353 --> 00:53:52,646
Put up with me a bit longer.

762
00:53:53,355 --> 00:53:54,481
You'll eventually beâ€¦

763
00:53:55,899 --> 00:53:56,983
the last one standing.

764
00:53:57,067 --> 00:53:59,277
Are you saying you won't end it now?

765
00:54:02,322 --> 00:54:03,782
How can you be so brazen?

766
00:54:03,865 --> 00:54:06,201
I can't make any plans
for summer next year.

767
00:54:07,619 --> 00:54:08,870
I won't be here.

768
00:54:08,954 --> 00:54:10,288
Are you emigrating?

769
00:54:12,874 --> 00:54:14,918
Stop making excuses--

770
00:54:15,001 --> 00:54:16,336
I'm not emigrating.

771
00:54:18,213 --> 00:54:19,589
I'll be dead by then.

772
00:54:22,258 --> 00:54:23,468
My days are numbered.

773
00:54:35,397 --> 00:54:36,231
I'm sorry.

774
00:54:57,961 --> 00:55:01,673
Mi-jo. Did you hear?
Dr. Kim doesn't need to go to the States.

775
00:55:02,340 --> 00:55:03,299
I heard.

776
00:55:04,009 --> 00:55:05,176
Why the long face?

777
00:55:07,429 --> 00:55:10,640
I can tell something's wrong.
What is it? Tell me.

778
00:55:11,683 --> 00:55:12,976
I'm just tired.

779
00:55:13,059 --> 00:55:14,602
You can't fool me.

780
00:55:14,686 --> 00:55:16,104
You're not tired.

781
00:55:17,105 --> 00:55:18,732
A lot of things happened.

782
00:55:19,399 --> 00:55:22,861
Chan-young's parents found out everything.

783
00:55:24,654 --> 00:55:26,489
I feel so bad for them.

784
00:55:26,573 --> 00:55:28,825
It's a good thing. They should know.

785
00:55:29,451 --> 00:55:33,538
I get that Chan-young's sick,
but you're about to fall ill too.

786
00:55:34,539 --> 00:55:36,374
You should get a vitamin shot.

787
00:55:36,958 --> 00:55:38,960
I'll think about it. You should go home.

788
00:55:39,461 --> 00:55:40,962
You too, Dr. Kim.

789
00:55:41,046 --> 00:55:43,381
Come have dinner with us.

790
00:55:43,465 --> 00:55:44,382
I'm not hungry.

791
00:55:44,466 --> 00:55:47,218
You should eat. You look worn out.

792
00:55:47,302 --> 00:55:49,846
He's right. Let's go grab a bite to eat.

793
00:55:49,929 --> 00:55:52,307
Come on. I don't want to eat alone.

794
00:55:52,390 --> 00:55:53,892
Please justâ€¦

795
00:55:53,975 --> 00:55:55,560
Just let me get some rest.

796
00:56:01,107 --> 00:56:03,193
Then make sure you drive safely, okay?

797
00:56:03,860 --> 00:56:05,612
Go take a bath or something.

798
00:56:05,695 --> 00:56:08,281
Okay, I will. I'm sorry.

799
00:56:09,199 --> 00:56:10,325
Don't be sorry.

800
00:56:10,950 --> 00:56:11,910
I'll be off now.

801
00:56:18,958 --> 00:56:20,126
Let's go home.

802
00:56:26,174 --> 00:56:29,135
Are you angry or sad?

803
00:56:37,602 --> 00:56:38,603
Let's go for a run.

804
00:56:58,414 --> 00:56:59,415
Mi-jo.

805
00:56:59,916 --> 00:57:03,336
Although you never grew inside my belly,

806
00:57:04,379 --> 00:57:06,631
I cared for you as if you did.

807
00:57:08,007 --> 00:57:09,676
That's pretty much the same thing.

808
00:57:10,218 --> 00:57:13,638
Whether or not I was pregnant with you
doesn't really matter.

809
00:57:15,390 --> 00:57:16,349
Because you were

810
00:57:17,142 --> 00:57:18,768
so beautiful and pure-hearted.

811
00:57:18,852 --> 00:57:20,395
INMATE NUMBER 2382, LEE GYEONG-SUK

812
00:57:36,161 --> 00:57:39,080
That's enough. You might get injured.

813
00:57:39,956 --> 00:57:41,666
You said running would clear my head.

814
00:57:42,167 --> 00:57:43,835
But it's still a mess.

815
00:57:43,918 --> 00:57:46,796
-Let's keep running.
-Then how about we take a break?

816
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:49,007
Sit down for a bit. Sit down.

817
00:57:49,090 --> 00:57:50,258
Why did you do that?

818
00:57:52,302 --> 00:57:53,136
What?

819
00:57:54,262 --> 00:57:55,889
I get that you were taken aback,

820
00:57:56,556 --> 00:58:00,185
but did you hate to have dinner
with my parents that much?

821
00:58:01,436 --> 00:58:04,189
Oh, that. Mi-jo, that was because--

822
00:58:04,272 --> 00:58:05,690
I didn't want to either.

823
00:58:05,773 --> 00:58:08,651
Why would I want
to introduce you to my parents?

824
00:58:10,069 --> 00:58:13,156
Don't say things you don't mean.
You'll end up regretting it.

825
00:58:13,239 --> 00:58:14,365
Do I embarrass you?

826
00:58:16,159 --> 00:58:17,452
Because I'm an orphan?

827
00:58:18,912 --> 00:58:20,121
Because I was adopted?

828
00:58:20,705 --> 00:58:21,706
Cha Mi-jo.

829
00:58:21,789 --> 00:58:25,251
What? Are you scared
things might get serious?

830
00:58:26,044 --> 00:58:29,088
Because you don't know
who my biological parents are?

831
00:58:29,672 --> 00:58:30,840
Does that scare you now?

832
00:58:32,842 --> 00:58:36,554
Get off me! Let go of me!

833
00:58:36,638 --> 00:58:38,431
-I'm sorry.
-Let go.

834
00:58:39,224 --> 00:58:41,601
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

835
00:58:42,769 --> 00:58:44,270
Why did you react like that?

836
00:58:46,439 --> 00:58:47,982
Why did you do that?

837
00:58:48,066 --> 00:58:50,944
I didn't mean it that way.
You were mistaken, Mi-jo.

838
00:58:52,278 --> 00:58:53,738
Why did you do that?

839
00:58:56,866 --> 00:58:57,825
It's because

840
00:58:58,701 --> 00:59:00,703
I love you so much.

841
00:59:04,666 --> 00:59:05,708
That's why.

842
00:59:16,761 --> 00:59:19,180
I didn't think I deserved you.

843
00:59:20,598 --> 00:59:23,935
I didn't think
I should meet your parents like this.

844
00:59:24,602 --> 00:59:26,437
I was ashamed to be my father's son.

845
00:59:28,106 --> 00:59:29,691
I wasn't confident.

846
00:59:29,774 --> 00:59:32,527
That's why I reacted that way. I'm sorry.

847
00:59:35,280 --> 00:59:37,365
I'm sorry I didn't explain.

848
00:59:39,701 --> 00:59:41,202
I'm sorry, okay?

849
00:59:44,539 --> 00:59:45,456
I'm sorry.

850
01:00:01,556 --> 01:00:02,890
I'm thirsty.

851
01:00:04,517 --> 01:00:05,518
Me too.

852
01:00:07,562 --> 01:00:08,563
Let's go.

853
01:00:33,087 --> 01:00:36,674
What do you think
my parents are thinking right now?

854
01:00:39,969 --> 01:00:41,679
They're probably worrying about you.

855
01:00:46,309 --> 01:00:48,061
My life is like a comedy.

856
01:00:48,728 --> 01:00:51,689
She threw a rolling pin at me,

857
01:00:51,773 --> 01:00:54,025
and she even hit me with vegetables.

858
01:00:54,108 --> 01:00:58,279
Gosh, I should've been there to see it.
It's a pity that I wasn't there.

859
01:00:58,363 --> 01:01:00,990
If you were there,
she would've beaten you up.

860
01:01:05,536 --> 01:01:07,622
I guess I deserve it.

861
01:01:09,916 --> 01:01:12,377
If that's what it takes to be forgiven.

862
01:01:16,881 --> 01:01:18,383
-Jin-seok.
-Yes?

863
01:01:20,968 --> 01:01:22,303
Don't get divorced.

864
01:01:26,891 --> 01:01:28,101
That's not your concern.

865
01:01:29,018 --> 01:01:31,979
Jin-seok, I want usâ€¦

866
01:01:37,193 --> 01:01:40,071
to part as friends, not lovers.

867
01:01:45,618 --> 01:01:46,744
Let's think about it.

868
01:01:50,998 --> 01:01:52,417
I want to go home alone.

869
01:02:16,983 --> 01:02:19,110
Here. Have something warm.

870
01:02:27,034 --> 01:02:28,703
What did So-won say?

871
01:02:28,786 --> 01:02:31,330
She says she's fine, but I'm not sure.

872
01:02:34,167 --> 01:02:37,253
I'm disappointed in your father.

873
01:02:40,923 --> 01:02:43,968
I just noticed
that we both stopped using honorifics.

874
01:02:44,051 --> 01:02:45,136
It's really nice.

875
01:02:46,095 --> 01:02:47,263
I don't know about that.

876
01:02:47,346 --> 01:02:48,222
Keep doing it.

877
01:02:48,306 --> 01:02:49,515
Do what?

878
01:02:49,599 --> 01:02:50,892
Talking without honorifics.

879
01:02:52,351 --> 01:02:55,354
What's the matter?
I can tell something's bothering you.

880
01:02:55,438 --> 01:02:57,398
You're thinking about something.

881
01:02:57,482 --> 01:02:59,233
You made it sound a certain way.

882
01:02:59,817 --> 01:03:02,195
You should've been clearer
about the subject.

883
01:03:02,278 --> 01:03:03,488
You made it sound vague.

884
01:03:04,071 --> 01:03:06,949
I guess you feel better now.
I'm going to go ahead and eat.

885
01:03:11,329 --> 01:03:12,580
Did you meet your father?

886
01:03:13,247 --> 01:03:14,165
Yes.

887
01:03:14,665 --> 01:03:15,750
What did you say?

888
01:03:16,626 --> 01:03:18,336
I told him to apologize to So-won.

889
01:03:18,419 --> 01:03:19,670
And?

890
01:03:20,797 --> 01:03:23,090
He's not willing to.
I hoped I could convince him.

891
01:03:24,217 --> 01:03:26,010
I told him I won't see him again

892
01:03:27,094 --> 01:03:28,596
if he doesn't apologize to her.

893
01:03:30,264 --> 01:03:32,433
I need to make a ton of money now.

894
01:03:32,517 --> 01:03:36,187
I told him I'd pay him back
every penny he's spent on me.

895
01:03:37,647 --> 01:03:38,898
It turns outâ€¦

896
01:03:40,483 --> 01:03:42,151
he spent a fortune raising me.

897
01:03:44,153 --> 01:03:45,363
You'll need a raise.

898
01:03:45,947 --> 01:03:46,906
I won't refuse.

899
01:03:58,292 --> 01:03:59,293
I have

900
01:04:00,545 --> 01:04:01,963
a new dream.

901
01:04:02,547 --> 01:04:04,340
You're almost 40, and you have a dream?

902
01:04:04,423 --> 01:04:06,133
After I pay my father back,

903
01:04:06,676 --> 01:04:08,636
I'm going to keep making lots of money.

904
01:04:08,719 --> 01:04:12,265
I'll save up
and buy my own land outside the city.

905
01:04:12,348 --> 01:04:15,643
Then I'm going to build a house
and adopt as many orphans as possible.

906
01:04:15,726 --> 01:04:17,979
I'll have a huge family.
What do you think?

907
01:04:18,646 --> 01:04:20,648
You'll have to make a lot of money.

908
01:04:20,731 --> 01:04:21,941
But that's not the issue.

909
01:04:22,024 --> 01:04:24,569
No matter how rich I become,
I won't be able to adopt.

910
01:04:25,611 --> 01:04:28,281
Apparently,
I need to have a stable family.

911
01:04:30,908 --> 01:04:34,453
So I need to get married.

912
01:04:35,162 --> 01:04:37,331
In conclusion, my dream isâ€¦

913
01:04:38,666 --> 01:04:40,251
that I want to beâ€¦

914
01:04:41,836 --> 01:04:43,462
your husband.

915
01:04:45,965 --> 01:04:46,799
Whatâ€¦

916
01:04:51,304 --> 01:04:54,682
Is this how people propose in America?

917
01:04:54,765 --> 01:04:57,476
No, I came up with this on my own.

918
01:04:58,102 --> 01:05:01,272
You know you can be
a little rash sometimes, right?

919
01:05:02,440 --> 01:05:04,775
One of us needs to be rash
to push things ahead.

920
01:05:08,112 --> 01:05:11,866
How about we go somewhere
and celebrate with some soju?

921
01:05:13,451 --> 01:05:14,660
Celebrate what?

922
01:05:15,202 --> 01:05:16,412
I'm not interested.

923
01:05:17,705 --> 01:05:21,500
It's just a small wish of mine.
I told you that it's my dream.

924
01:05:21,584 --> 01:05:23,586
Don't feel pressured. Okay?

925
01:05:24,754 --> 01:05:28,925
It's drizzling outside,
so I figured we could drink some soju.

926
01:05:32,553 --> 01:05:34,347
Not tonight.

927
01:05:35,598 --> 01:05:37,350
My head isn't clear yet.

928
01:05:39,143 --> 01:05:42,313
I'll drink once things are settled.

929
01:05:44,649 --> 01:05:45,650
Try this.

930
01:06:02,750 --> 01:06:06,879
You called us here this early.
Why aren't you saying anything?

931
01:06:08,589 --> 01:06:10,007
It's about something important.

932
01:06:11,384 --> 01:06:13,010
Let's wait until everyone's gone.

933
01:06:16,931 --> 01:06:18,849
-Hey.
-Hey, Seon-u.

934
01:06:18,933 --> 01:06:20,393
-Is business doing well?
-Yes.

935
01:06:22,520 --> 01:06:24,438
It's strange that she called all of us.

936
01:06:24,522 --> 01:06:26,273
What's with that serious look?

937
01:06:26,357 --> 01:06:27,233
Long time no see.

938
01:06:27,316 --> 01:06:29,193
Hey. You've become even more handsome.

939
01:06:29,276 --> 01:06:31,570
-Thanks.
-Don't say things you don't mean.

940
01:06:32,238 --> 01:06:34,156
Chan-young, you look prettier than ever.

941
01:06:34,240 --> 01:06:35,866
-I know that.
-I see.

942
01:06:38,661 --> 01:06:40,079
Just tell us.

943
01:06:40,162 --> 01:06:41,247
Why did you call us?

944
01:06:44,667 --> 01:06:48,004
Why couldn't you just ask us
to meet in your clinic where it's quiet?

945
01:06:48,087 --> 01:06:48,921
I know, right?

946
01:07:12,236 --> 01:07:14,155
-Seon-u.
-Yes?

947
01:07:14,238 --> 01:07:16,240
Can you please sit next to Joo-hee?

948
01:07:22,830 --> 01:07:23,831
Sure.

949
01:07:32,214 --> 01:07:33,174
What's going on?

950
01:07:33,257 --> 01:07:34,759
It's really important.

951
01:07:37,762 --> 01:07:42,767
Chan-young and Seon-u.
Can you both lock arms with Joo-hee?

952
01:07:43,934 --> 01:07:44,894
I'm going to leave.

953
01:07:45,561 --> 01:07:47,354
I'm serious right now.

954
01:07:47,438 --> 01:07:48,939
Just do what I ask.

955
01:07:51,692 --> 01:07:54,445
Goodness, you're nuts. Like this?

956
01:07:55,780 --> 01:07:56,614
Seon-u, you too.

957
01:07:59,116 --> 01:08:00,117
Excuse me for a bit.

958
01:08:03,329 --> 01:08:05,998
What is this?
It feels like I'm getting arrested.

959
01:08:07,792 --> 01:08:09,001
I have shocking news.

960
01:08:12,630 --> 01:08:14,965
I found my biological mother.

961
01:08:17,301 --> 01:08:19,053
-My gosh. That's great.
-Goodness.

962
01:08:19,136 --> 01:08:20,387
What? When?

963
01:08:20,471 --> 01:08:21,555
Keep your arms locked.

964
01:08:21,639 --> 01:08:24,225
Oh, right. Okay. Keep going.

965
01:08:24,308 --> 01:08:26,560
How? How did you find her?

966
01:08:27,144 --> 01:08:28,687
Hold on tight to Joo-hee.

967
01:08:28,771 --> 01:08:29,814
Okay.

968
01:08:31,148 --> 01:08:32,775
Joo-hee's momâ€¦

969
01:08:34,026 --> 01:08:34,944
told me.

970
01:08:39,323 --> 01:08:42,409
Apparently, she's known for a long time.

971
01:08:43,744 --> 01:08:44,578
Hold onto her.

972
01:08:48,332 --> 01:08:50,876
-Take her phone away.
-Come on!

973
01:08:54,713 --> 01:08:55,881
My biological motherâ€¦

974
01:08:57,883 --> 01:08:59,760
has been convicted of fraud seven times.

975
01:09:00,761 --> 01:09:04,348
She's still doing time in prison.

976
01:09:08,269 --> 01:09:10,104
Are you scared things might get serious?

977
01:09:10,187 --> 01:09:13,190
Because you don't know
who my biological parents are?

978
01:09:13,774 --> 01:09:15,109
Does that scare you now?

979
01:09:23,242 --> 01:09:25,911
Seon-u, I'm not done talking yet.

980
01:09:27,121 --> 01:09:28,122
Okay.

981
01:09:32,001 --> 01:09:35,212
So I've decided to pay her a visit.

982
01:09:35,754 --> 01:09:36,630
At Yeongwol Prison.

983
01:09:40,759 --> 01:09:43,470
But as you probably know,
I have panic disorder.

984
01:09:44,763 --> 01:09:47,349
If I get flustered
and end up getting a panic attack,

985
01:09:47,433 --> 01:09:49,018
I might not be able to drive.

986
01:09:50,561 --> 01:09:51,604
Who will come with me?

987
01:09:51,687 --> 01:09:52,646
Me.

988
01:10:10,080 --> 01:10:12,499
I hope Mi-jo doesn't collapse

989
01:10:13,459 --> 01:10:14,752
because of a panic attack.

990
01:10:16,545 --> 01:10:18,547
I should've gone with her.

991
01:10:18,631 --> 01:10:21,342
We should've given her relaxing pills.

992
01:10:23,427 --> 01:10:26,764
I was reminded of when I met Mi-jo
for the first time on the subway.

993
01:10:27,681 --> 01:10:29,642
The day she went
looking for her biological mother.

994
01:10:29,725 --> 01:10:30,976
YEONGWOL PRISON

995
01:10:31,060 --> 01:10:32,019
Hey.

996
01:10:33,020 --> 01:10:34,521
Why is she out already?

997
01:10:41,737 --> 01:10:43,072
She doesn't look too good.

998
01:10:43,739 --> 01:10:45,157
Did she not get to meet her?

999
01:10:50,663 --> 01:10:52,623
We never let it show,

1000
01:10:53,582 --> 01:10:56,627
but we were all desperate
to hear about her biological mother.

1001
01:10:59,338 --> 01:11:00,214
Mi-jo.

1002
01:11:13,811 --> 01:11:14,895
Mi-jo.

1003
01:11:14,979 --> 01:11:16,814
What's wrong?

1004
01:11:34,707 --> 01:11:37,793
Although it felt like a blessing
that the day came before I died,

1005
01:11:40,671 --> 01:11:43,882
I had no idea it would be
so heartbreaking for all of us.

1006
01:11:54,184 --> 01:12:01,191
TRUSTWORTHY LAW
HAPPY YEONGWOL

1007
01:12:37,436 --> 01:12:40,272
Though I didn't have high expectationsâ€¦

1008
01:12:40,356 --> 01:12:41,982
It bothers me.

1009
01:12:44,985 --> 01:12:48,489
I'll let you know every day

1010
01:12:49,031 --> 01:12:52,284
how much I love you.

1011
01:12:52,368 --> 01:12:55,371
It's my mom's last birthday
that I'll get to see.

1012
01:12:55,454 --> 01:12:57,081
Do you desperately want that?

1013
01:12:58,332 --> 01:13:00,584
So what if I'll be alone?

1014
01:13:00,667 --> 01:13:02,503
Every single day is so precious.

1015
01:13:02,586 --> 01:13:06,799
It's hard to be
the happiest terminally ill person.

1016
